Source: mt32emu-alsadrv
Section: contrib/sound
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Vincent Crevot <vcrevot@retroject.net>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 7), mt32emu-dev (>= 0.1.3), libasound2-dev, libxt-dev, libxpm-dev
Standards-Version: 3.8.0
Homepage: http://sourceforge.net/projects/munt/

Package: mt32emu-mt32d
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Suggests: dosbox, alsa-utils
Description: Roland MT-32 emulator
 This package provides an user-space ALSA MIDI driver which emulates the Roland
 MT-32, CM-32L and LAPC-I synthesizer modules. These devices were used by many
 DOS games from the 80's and 90's to produce digital music and sound effects.
 .
 This is the headless version. See the mt32emu-xmt32 package for the X11
 version.
 .
 NOTE: you must own a dump of the original Roland ROM for this package to be of
 any practical use.

Package: mt32emu-xmt32
Architecture: any
Suggests: dosbox, alsa-utils
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Roland MT-32 emulator for X11
 This package provides an user-space ALSA MIDI driver which emulates the Roland
 MT-32, CM-32L and LAPC-I synthesizer modules. These devices were used by many
 DOS games from the 80's and 90's to produce digital music and sound effects.
 .
 This is the X11 version, complete with a fake MT-32 front-panel and LCD
 display. It is however quite UNSTABLE in its current state. See the
 mt32emu-mt32d package for the headless version.
 .
 NOTE: you must own a dump of the original Roland ROM for this package to be of
 any practical use.
